data.chText: 现世的；世俗的；非宗教的
data.enText: not connected with spiritual or religious matters

data.chText: 我们的社会是个世俗社会。

data.enText: living among ordinary people rather than in a religious community

tr: someone who is not a clergyman or a professional person
of or relating to clergy not bound by monastic vows
not concerned with or devoted to religion
example: secular architecture", "children being brought up in an entirely profane environment

tr: characteristic of those who are not members of the clergy
example: set his collar in laic rather than clerical position

tr: characteristic of or devoted to the temporal world as opposed to the spiritual world
of or relating to the doctrine that rejects religion and religious considerations

value.def: You use secular to describe things that have no connection with religion.

example.ex: He spoke about preserving the country as a secular state.
example.tran: 他谈及了保持该国世俗化的问题。

value.tran: 世俗的;现世的;非宗教的
